<1ST_LINE>d a PM-People-Zaccaro     07-15 0110</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Zaccaro,0113</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>RUTLAND, Vt. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John Zaccaro Jr., the son of former vice
presidential candidate Geraldine Ferraro, is appealing his
conviction for selling $25 worth of cocaine to an undercover
officer.
   Attorneys for Zaccaro filed the brief notice in Vermont District
Court in Rutland on Thursday, indicating an appeal of both
Zaccaro's conviction and sentence, said Court Clerk Ann Dingler.
   The case now goes to the Vermont Supreme Court for final review.
   Zaccaro, 24, has already begun serving his four-month sentence
under a special house arrest program.
   The former Middlebury College student was convicted in April by
a jury of selling the drug to former Trooper Laura Manning.
