<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rock star Michael Jackson launched his first
British tour with a spectacular two-hour concert during which he
rode over the heads of 72,000 screaming fans in a cradle suspended
from a crane.
   ``Shall I come down there?'' he teased as he dangled within
inches of their outstretched arms at London's Wembley Stadium on
Thursday night.
   But he didn't, confining himself instead to blowing kisses at
the fans and telling them, ``I love you.''
   During the performance, the 29-year-old star repeatedly
disappeared in puffs of smoke and behind silver curtains, only to
reappear seconds later hundreds of feet away.
   Among entertainers in the audience were British pop stars Boy
George and Terence Trent D'Arby and singer Diana Ross.
