<1ST_LINE>r a PM-SocialSpat     07-15 0205</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Social Spat,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Social Register Puts Down Nouveau Rival</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   PALM BEACH, Fla. _ A social register that for 67 years has
helped the elite sort out who is who among South Florida's
prominent residents has fought off a nouveau rival, its attorneys
said.
   The Social Index-Directory last month filed suit against The
Palm Beach Social Index, claiming the publication incorporated May
16 had a name so similar that it would confuse subscribers.
   But a hearing scheduled for Thursday was canceled when The
Social Index agreed to change its name to the Palm Beach Society
Blue Book and print a retraction of a June 10 news release in which
it made several disputed statements about the Index-Directory.
   ``We're 100 percent vindicated and 100 percent victorious,''
said Andrew Rafkin, the Index-Directory's attorney. ``We got
everything we wanted, which is not usual.''
   Index-Directory publisher Susan Kennedy said she did not mind
competition but said she didn't want people to be confused between
the two publications. Haley Ennis, publisher of what is now the
Blue Book, said she and her colleagues had not meant to insult the
Index-Directory's new owners.
   Both registers plan to publish listings of socially connected
people in the Bahamas and South Florida before Christmas.
</TEXT>
