<HEAD>Briton Charged With Running Mail-Order Bride Business Without
License</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Government agents arrested a British
man on charges of running a mail-order-bride business without a
proper business license, immigration officials said today.
   Ponciano Ortiz, an intelligence officer at the Commission on
Immigration and Deportation, said Vincent Charles Browne ``will
definitely be deported,'' but did not specify any date.
   Ortiz said in a telephone interview that Browne was arrested
Thursday in an office at the Manila suburb of Makati where he
allegedly recruited Filipino women as prospective brides for
clients in Britain.
   A report in the Philippine Daily Globe quoted Browne as saying
he was not aware that he had violated any laws since his office was
an ``ordinary introduction agency.''
   No formal charges have been filed against Browne, who was being
held in a detention center for foreigners awaiting deportation.
