<HEAD>Former Prostitute Returns Home After Swaggart Saga</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PATOKA, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Debra Murphree, the prostitute who bared her
soul and much more about fallen television evangelist Jimmy
Swaggart, has returned to her home town to live with her parents.
   Ms. Murphree, 28, said she plans to earn a high school
equivalency degree and become an interior decorator.
   ``Everybody's happy to see me home,'' said Ms. Murphree, after
recently completing a 10-city tour promoting her story. ``Nobody's
said anything to me, you know, rough or anything.''
   Earlier this year, Ms. Murphree said Swaggart paid her $20 a
visit and asked her to pose naked, talk dirty and perform other
acts. Swaggart has declined to answer any of her allegations.
   She has since told her story on ``Donahue,'' ``Larry King'' and
``Geraldo.'' Penthouse Magazine reportedly paid her between $75,000
and $100,000 to recreate the poses she said Swaggart paid her to
assume.
   The Assemblies of God ultimately defrocked Swaggart after he
acknowledged Feb. 21 that he had committed an unspecified sin and
then refused to accept the denomination's recommendation that he
take a year off from preaching.
