<HEAD>Heavy Storms in Drought-Hit Midwest</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 9th graf, ``Temperatures around ...,'' to fix garble.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Powerful thunderstorms rumbled through sections of the
drought-battered Midwest today, triggering a flash flood watch in
southwest Nebraska, after storms in the Northeast toppled a barn
and downed power lines.
   Thunderstorms dropped heavy rain on Nebraska, and were building
in eastern North Dakota and northern Minnesota, where a severe
thunderstorm watch was in effect this morning.
   On Thursday, strong thunderstorms slapped New York state, New
Jersey, Connecticut, Massachusetts, Vermont and New Hampshire,
knocking down trees and power lines.
   High winds toppled a barn in Winchendon, Mass., and overturned a
60-foot-long trailer and blew a roof off a house in Bethel, N.Y.
Hail fell in Goshen and Sussex, N.J., and 4 inches of rain fell in
one hour in Agawam, Mass.
   In the Midwest, powerful storms Thursday generated a tornado
that hit near Palisade in southwest Nebraska, winds gusting to 75
mph and 1}-inch hail in Gothenburg, Neb.
   Thunderstorms in the drought-hit Ohio Valley downed trees in
Indiana, and dropped hail up to an inch in diameter in Ohio and
Illinois.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
in Florida, widely scattered showers and thunderstorms in upper
Michigan, Wisconsin, northern Illinois, northeast Iowa and eastern
Minnesota.
   High temperatures were predicted in the 70s and 80s from New
England to the lower Great Lakes, Michigan, northern Wisconsin and
Minnesota, and from Montana to the northern Pacific Coast; the
upper 60s to the low 80s along the California coast; in the upper
90s to more than 100 degrees from Illinois to Missouri and the
southern two-thirds of the Plains; near 115 degrees in eastern
California and the desert Southwest; and the 90s in the rest of the
nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 46
degrees at Kalispell, Mont., to 95 at Phoenix, Ariz., and Luke Air
Force Base at Glendale, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 74 fair; Boston 74 partly cloudy; Buffalo 66
fair; Charleston, S.C. 78 foggy; Cincinnati 76 foggy; Cleveland 73
fair; Detroit 71 fair; Miami 74 fair; New York 75 partly cloudy;
Philadelphia 81 cloudy; Pittsburgh 75 foggy; Portland, Maine 69
foggy; Washington 81 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 83 fair; Chicago 79 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
85 windy; Denver 68 fair; Des Moines 79 fair; Indianapolis 69 fair;
Kansas City 85 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 82 partly cloudy; New
Orleans 80 fair; St. Louis 86 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 71 fair; Anchorage 60 cloudy; Las Vegas 87
fair; Phoenix 95 fair; Salt Lake City 78 fair; San Diego 66 cloudy;
San Francisco 59 windy; Seattle 58 cloudy.
   _Canada: Toronto 61 fair.
</TEXT>
