<2ND_LINE>PM-Venezuela-Plane Crash,0162</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Plane Crash Kills 10 In Venezuela</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A two-engine plane crashed in a jungle
in southern Venezuela and killed 10 of the 11 people on board,
authorities said today. A 5-year-old boy survived, they said.
   The boy, Remy Revilla, suffered serious burns and was
hospitalized in critical condition in Ciudad Bolivar, civil
aeronautics officials said. Ciudad Bolivar is 280 miles east of the
capital, Caracas.
   The boy's father was killed in the crash Thursday, the officials
said.
   Rescue patrols sent to the area said most of the bodies were
burned beyond recognition.
   The plane took off before noon from Ciudad Bolivar and was
headed to Icabaru, near the Brazilian border. Most of the
passengers, including four musicians, were to attend a party in
Icabaru.
   A few minutes after takeoff, the pilot reported failure in one
of the engines.
   ``Nothing was heard since from the pilot,'' a civil aeronautics
official said.
</TEXT>
