<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Thailand-Weapons     07-15 0119</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Thailand-Weapons,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Seize Weapons Before Thai Elections</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities have seized hundreds of
rifles, grenades and other weapons in a nationwide crackdown to
ensure law and order during the July 24 general election, a police
official said Friday.
   Most of the weapons were seized in Chantaburi, Prachinburi and
Kanchanaburi provinces on Thailand's troubled borders with Cambodia
and Burma, said Lt. Col. Nopporn Sangsuwan of the Provincial Police
Policy and Planning Board.
   Police seized more than 1,700 rifles, including M-16s, 112 hand
grenades and 10,413 rounds of ammunition, he said.
   The general election was scheduled after Prime Minister Prem
Tinsulanonda dissolved Parliament in April when the main party in
his governing coalition challenged his policies.
</TEXT>
