<HEAD>Marine Sentenced To Year In Prison For Homosexual Acts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARRIS ISLAND, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Marine drill instructor was
sentenced today to a year in prison for having lesbian relations
with two other soldiers.
   Sgt. Cheryl Jameson, 27, of Napa, Calif., also was reduced to a
private, dishonorably discharged and forced to forfeit all pay and
benefits.
   The nine-year member of the corps is the second Marine given a
prison sentence in the ongoing investigation into lesbianism at the
Marine boot camp at Parris Island. Six women have been charged with
indecent acts in the case.
   Ms. Jameson pleaded guilty to committing indecent acts with
Staff Sgt. Bonnie Ferguson and fraternizing and committing indecent
acts with Lance Cpl. Carie Prusa before and after Ms. Prusa
completed boot camp.
