<1ST_LINE>r a AM-SteakThief     07-15 0257</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Steak Thief,0264</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Burglar Takes Steaks _ Nine Times</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A burglar has been serving himself at a
restaurant, repeatedly making off with 14-ounce steaks from the
freezer, and the owner is cooking up a stakeout.
   ``That's all they take is steak. I just don't know what to think
any more, because they've gotten away with a lot of it lots of
times,'' said Tommy C. Hamby, owner of The Hoffbrau.
   The steakhouse was burglarized this week for the ninth time this
year, police said. Hamby said the haul has totaled hundreds of
steaks.
   Police are interviewing witnesses, Sgt. Jerold Seidl said.
``There appears to be a pattern. It sounds like someone is getting
full on steak.''
   Sixty 14-ounce, top sirloin steaks were taken after 11:30 p.m.
Wednesday, when someone broke in through the front window of the
restaurant.
   ``The alarm went off when he broke the window, but he went
straight to the icebox and got out before police got here,'' Hamby
said. ``He's pretty brave to do that on Sixth Street on a busy
night.''
   Hamby said 50 to more than 100 steaks have been taken each time
the restaurant has been hit, and the thief also has broken in
through the ceiling and the kitchen window.
   ``I had to put burglar bars on the side windows and would rather
not do that to the front, but I may have to because it's running up
there,'' Hamby said.
   He estimated his losses at $5,000 to $7,000, including repairs
on broken windows.
</TEXT>
