<HEAD>Two Suspected Guerrillas Killed In National Park</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soldiers killed two suspected
African National Congress guerrillas in Kruger National Park
following an explosion which damaged a park vehicle, military
headquarters said Friday.
   The suspects were killed Thursday during a combined army-air
force operation launched after the explosion Monday in a
far-northern section of the park near the border with Mozambique.
   Military headquarters said weapons were seized during the
operation but gave no other details.
   Tol Pienaar, chief executive of the National Parks Board, said
he believed it was still safe for tourists to visit Kruger, the
country's largest national park.
</TEXT>
