<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Jenny Seagrove, who recently starred in
the TV miniseries ``A Woman of Substance,'' was granted a divorce
Friday from a man the judge said trapped her in an emotional web
and made her totally dependent on him.
   Divorce Court Judge Clive Callman said actor Madhav Sharma had
failed to become a star in his own right, exercised a hypnotic
power over his 30-year-old wife and used her success to force
himself into the limelight.
   He said Sharma, 47, ``has an extraordinary, almost hypnotic
power over people and was Svengali to Jenny Seagrove'' for half
their four-year marriage.
