<TEXT>
   What could comedian Jay Leno and
millionaire publisher Malcolm Forbes possibly have in common?
   Money? Senses of humor?
   But it was their love of motorcycles that brought them together
Thursday night at Caesars Palace.
   Forbes, who publishes Forbes magazine, stopped in Las Vegas
while on an 1,800-mile motorcycle ride from his Colorado ranch to
Los Angeles.
   The millionaire is scheduled to appear as Leno's guest on the
``Tonight Show'' in Burbank on Monday night.
   Forbes first appeared on the show as Leno's guest in 1985, and
the two have become friends. Both share an interest in motorcycles,
and they drew a crowd when they checked out the cycles used by
Forbes and his seven-person entourage on their cross-country ride.
   The 69-year-old Forbes said he began riding a motorcycle 21
years ago.
   He joked that he had a ``deprived childhood'' and didn't get a
motorcycle until he was 48.
