<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Iran-Canada     07-15 0136</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Iran-Canada,0141</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Canadian Delegation Visits Iran</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Gulf Rdp</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Canadian delegation is in Iran to
discuss the possible normalization of diplomatic relations severed
in 1980, according to a brief report by Tehran radio.
   The report, monitored in Britain, said the Canadians arrived
Friday but gave no details.
   Canada closed its embassy in Tehran in 1980 in the furor over
the holding of 52 American hostages at the U.S. Embassy for 444
days. The captives were freed and flew home in January 1980.
   Iran had denounced Canada for sheltering a few Americans in the
Canadian Embassy during the hostage crisis.
   Denmark handled Canadian interests in Iran after diplomatic
relations were broken.
   Indications have emerged that Iran, at war with Iraq since
September 1980, is trying to improve relations with other countries.
</TEXT>
