criminal charges that it has managed just two successful
prosecutions of safety violators since 1980, said a report on the
study by The National Safe Workplace Institute.
   During the same period, California successfully prosecuted 112
cases under state operation of the federally funded program, the
institute found. California has since dropped its program, and
supporters are seeking its reinstatement.
